O%20territory%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226692%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6583a17dcefc010bea25f3c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin.%3Cp%3EContributor%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20ex-CIA%20analyst%20says%20Russia%20might%20risk%20nuclear%20war%20with%20NATO%20to%20prevail%20in%20their%20war%20with%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPeter%20Schroeder%20says%20Putin%20has%20been%C2%A0%26quot%3Bremarkably%20consistent%26quot%3B%20about%20using%20nuclear%20weapons%20on%20NATO.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPutin%20said%20recently%20that%20Russia%20had%20no%20interest%20in%20fighting%20NATO%20forces.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20ex-CIA%20analyst%20says%20the%20US%20might%20be%20underestimating%20the%20possibility%20of%20nuclear%20war%20between%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-told-ukraine-to-scrap-nato-to-end-the-war%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussia%20and%20NATO%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20a%20mistake.%20US%20officials%20have%20it%20backward%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnas.org%2Fpeople%2Fpeter-schroeder%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeter%20Schroeder%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewrote%20in%20an%20article%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreignaffairs.com%2Fukraine%2Freal-russian-nuclear-threat%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EForeign%20Affairs%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20actually%20quite%20unlikely%20that%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20will%20use%20a%20nuclear%20weapon%20on%20the%20battlefield%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20it%20is%20very%20possible%20that%20he%20will%20move%20toward%20using%20one%20against%20NATO%2C%26quot%3B%20Schroeder%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20public%20servant%20spent%20nearly%20two%20decades%20working%20on%20issues%20relating%20to%20Russia.%20Besides%20working%20for%20the%20CIA%2C%20Schroeder%20had%20done%20stints%20at%20the%20US%20embassy%20in%20Moscow%20and%20the%20National%20Intelligence%20Council.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20Putin%20invokes%20his%20arsenal%2C%20he%20is%20not%20trying%20to%20warn%20that%20Russia%20could%20use%20tactical%20nuclear%20weapons%20in%20Ukraine.%20Rather%2C%20his%20rhetoric%20is%20designed%20to%20threaten%20NATO%20itself%2C%26quot%3B%20Schroeder%20said%20in%20his%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchroeder%20said%20that%20Putin%20wasn't%20just%20engaging%20in%20saber-rattling%20whenever%20he%20touted%20Russia's%20nuclear%20capabilities.%20He%20believes%20that%20going%20nuclear%20is%20something%20Putin%20could%20actually%20do%20if%20he%20wanted%20to%20win%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20swiftly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnlike%20the%20West%2C%20Putin%20may%20not%20fear%20a%20nuclear%20standoff%3A%20he%20is%20well-versed%20in%20Russia's%20nuclear%20arsenal%20and%20the%20tenets%20of%20nuclear%20deterrence%2C%20and%20possibly%20sees%20himself%20as%20uniquely%20suited%20to%20navigating%20a%20nuclear%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20Schroeder%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20Putin%20has%20been%20remarkably%20consistent%20that%20Russia%20is%20willing%20to%20use%20nuclear%20weapons%20against%20NATO%20to%20defend%20its%20interests%20in%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20referencing%20Putin's%20remarks%20eight%20years%20ago%20when%20he%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2015%2F03%2F16%2Feurope%2Frussia-putin-crimea-nuclear%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussia%20was%20ready%20to%20mobilize%20its%20nuclear%20forces%20during%20its%20invasion%20of%20Crimea%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchroeder%20then%20outlined%20how%20Putin%20could%20ratchet%20up%20Russia's%20pressure%20against%20NATO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Putin%20does%20escalate%20the%20war%2C%20for%20instance%20by%20attacking%20NATO%20with%20conventional%20weapons%2C%20he%20will%20likely%20move%20very%20swiftly%2C%20so%20as%20not%20to%20give%20the%20United%20States%20a%20chance%20to%20maneuver%20away%20from%20a%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20there%2C%20Moscow%20might%20actually%20begin%20using%20force%20against%20NATO%2C%26quot%3B%20Schroeder%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Russia%20could%20attack%20NATO%20aircraft%2C%20ships%2C%20and%20convoys%20to%20drag%20NATO%20into%20the%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFinally%2C%20in%20a%20worst-case%20scenario%E2%80%94one%20where%20the%20Kremlin%20sought%20to%20shock%20the%20world%20into%20ending%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20quickly%20and%20on%20Putin's%20terms%E2%80%94Russia%20could%20actually%20launch%20a%20nuclear%20weapon%20directly%20at%20NATO%20territory%2C%26quot%3B%20Schroeder%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20US%20and%20Russia%20have%20sought%20to%20downplay%20the%20possibility%20of%20nuclear%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20said%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20in%20Helsinki%20that%20there%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F07%2F13%2Frussia-ukraine-war-news%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewasn't%20any%20danger%20of%20Russia%20using%20nuclear%20weapons%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20there's%20any%20real%20prospect%2C%20you%20never%20know%2C%20of%20Putin%20using%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%26quot%3B%20Biden%20said%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20Russian%20leader%20Vladimir%20Putin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fputin-says-bidens-remark-about-russian-plan-attack-nato-is-complete-rubbish-2023-12-17%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrushed%20aside%20Biden's%20comments%20on%20how%20Russia%20would%20attack%20NATO%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20defeating%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia%20has%20no%20reason%2C%20no%20interest%2C%20no%20geopolitical%20interest%2C%20neither%20economic%2C%20political%20nor%20military%2C%20to%20fight%20with%20NATO%20countries%2C%26quot%3B%20Putin%20said%20in%20a%20televised%20interview%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20Schroeder%2C%20the%20White%20House%2C%20and%20the%20Russian%20foreign%20and%20defense%20ministries%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-cia-analyst-putin-could-use-nuclear-weapon-on-nato-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703130857000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6583a1bd1c5c7b8c9a0abc3f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-cia-analyst-putin-could-use-nuclear-weapon-on-nato-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BPutin%20has%20been%20remarkably%20consistent%20that%20Russia%20is%20willing%20to%20use%20nuclear%20weapons%20against%20NATO%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20former%20CIA%20analyst.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktan%40businessinsider.com%20(Kwan%20Wei%20Kevin%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A42%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-cia-analyst-putin-could-use-nuclear-weapon-on-nato-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Wrestling%20Body%20Polls%20Today%2C%20A%20Chief%20Minister%20Is%20Among%20Candidates%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20posts%20of%20Wrestling%20Federation%20of%20India%20(WFI)%2C%20which%20hit%20headlines%20over%20sexual%20harassment%20allegations%20against%20its%20chief%20and%20BJP%20MP%20Brij%20Bhushan%20Sharan%20Singh%2C%20are%20set%20to%20go%20to%20polls%20today.%20The%20contest%20for%20the%20president%20post%20is%20between%20Sanjay%20Singh%2C%20said%20to%20be%20close%20to%20Brij%20Bhushan%20Sharan%20Singh%2C%20and%20Commonwealth%20Games%20gold%20medallist%20Anita%20Sheoran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20the%20top%20post%2C%20polls%20will%20be%20hold%20to%20fill%20up%20posts%20for%20a%20senior%20vice-president%2C%20four%20vice-presidents%2C%20a%20secretary%20general%2C%20a%20treasurer%2C%20two%20joint%20secretaries%20and%20five%20executive%20members.%20Interestingly%2C%20one%20of%20the%20candidates%20for%20the%20vice-president%20post%20is%20newly%20appointed%20Chief%20Minister%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20a%20former%20wrestler%20-%20Mohan%20Yadav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday's%20election%20will%20give%20the%20country's%20top%20wrestling%20body%20a%20new%20president%20after%2012%20years%20of%20Brij%20Bhushan%20Sharan%20Singh%20occupying%20the%20top%20post.%20The%20BJP%20MP%20from%20Kaiserganj%20had%20to%20step%20aside%20after%20the%20country's%20top%20wrestlers%20led%20a%20protest%2C%20accusing%20him%20of%20sexually%20harassing%20women%20wrestlers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAce%20wrestlers%20Bajrang%20Punia%2C%20Sakshi%20Malik%20and%20Vinesh%20Phogat%2C%20who%20led%20the%20agitation%2C%20had%20been%20promised%20that%20none%20of%20Brij%20Bhushan%20Singh's%20family%20members%20or%20aides%20will%20be%20allowed%20to%20contest%20the%20elections.%20So%2C%20Brij%20Bhushan's%20son%20Prateek%20and%20son-in-law%20Vishal%20Singh%20did%20not%20enter%20the%20race%2C%20but%20his%20aide%20Sanjay%20Singh's%20nomination%20was%20cleared.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Sheoran%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20backed%20by%20wrestlers%20who%20participated%20in%20the%20protest%20against%20the%20long-time%20WFI%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Sanjay%20Singh%20and%20his%20associates%2C%20they%20have%20the%20support%20of%20wrestling%20federations%20from%20most%20states%20and%20are%20confident%20of%20a%20victory.%20The%20wrestling%20fraternity%2C%20he%20said%2C%20knows%20who%20worked%20for%20the%20betterment%20of%20sports%20and%20will%20keep%20it%20in%20mind%20while%20casting%20their%20vote.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20winning%20his%20election%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20NDTV%2C%20beaming%20with%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20Mr%20Yadav%20contesting%20the%20election%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20a%20wrestler%20has%20risen%20to%20become%20a%20Chief%20Minister%20of%20a%20state%20is%20a%20big%20message.%20I%20am%20sure%20he%20will%20win%20here%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20for%20the%20WFI%20election%20began%20in%20July%2C%20but%20court%20cases%20kept%20delaying%20it.%20This%20led%20to%20the%20international%20wrestling%20body%20suspending%20WFI.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20recently%20set%20aside%20a%20stay%20imposed%20by%20the%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20High%20Court%2C%20clearing%20the%20decks%20for%20the%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703130720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fn489cao_wfi-split_625x300_21_December_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsanjay-singh-anita-sheoran-brij-bhushan-sharan-singh-wfi-elections-wrestling-body-goes-to-polls-today-a-chief-minister-is-a-candidate-4713819%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20top%20posts%20of%20Wrestling%20Federation%20of%20India%20(WFI)%2C%20which%20hit%20headlines%20over%20sexual%20harassment%20allegations%20against%20its%20chief%20and%20BJP%20MP%20Brij%20Bhushan%20Sharan%20Singh%2C%20are%20set%20to%20go%20to%20polls%20today.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsanjay-singh-anita-sheoran-brij-bhushan-sharan-singh-wfi-elections-wrestling-body-goes-to-polls-today-a-chief-minister-is-a-candidate-4713819%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsanjay-singh-anita-sheoran-brij-bhushan-sharan-singh-wfi-elections-wrestling-body-goes-to-polls-today-a-chief-m