Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw31970%2Fw31970.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20working%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20researchers%20at%20USC%2C%20Columbia%2C%20Stanford%2C%20and%20Northwestern%2C%20assessing%20the%20impact%20of%20higher-for-longer%20interest%20rates%20on%20the%20commercial%20real%20estate%20industry%20and%20the%20US%20banking%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%2C%20titled%20%26quot%3BMonetary%20Tightening%2C%20Commercial%20Real%20Estate%20Distress%2C%20and%20US%20Bank%20Fragility%2C%26quot%3B%20used%20a%20framework%20developed%20earlier%20to%20examine%20the%20Fed's%20aggressive%20rate%20hikes%20in%202022%2C%20which%20weighed%20down%20assets%20like%20stocks%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Fbond-market-crash-jpmorgan-bank-of-america-unrealized-losses-explainer-2023-11%5C%22%3Ebonds%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20commercial%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20estimated%20that%20due%20to%20declines%20in%20property%20values%20from%20rate%20hikes%20and%20remote%20work%2C%20about%2014%25%20of%20all%20loans%20and%2044%25%20of%20office%20loans%20are%20in%20negative%20equity%2C%20meaning%20current%20values%20are%20less%20than%20outstanding%20loan%20balances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%2010%25-20%25%20of%20all%20commercial%20real%20estate%20loans%20could%20default%20%E2%80%94%20on%20the%20low%20end%20of%20what%20the%20default%20rate%20was%20estimated%20to%20be%20during%20the%20Great%20Financial%20Crisis%20%E2%80%94%20and%20banks%20could%20see%20around%20%24160%20billion%20in%20losses%2C%20according%20to%20the%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20evidence%20suggests%20that%20if%20interest%20rates%20remain%20elevated%20and%20property%20values%20do%20not%20recover%2C%20default%20rates%20could%20potentially%20reach%20levels%20comparing%20or%20even%20surp