4924%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Media%20Bodies%20Condemn%20IT%20Dept%20Freezing%20NewsClick%E2%80%99s%20Accounts%2C%20Say%20Move%20Flouts%20Basic%20Norms%20of%20Labour%20Laws%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F07130338%2FUntitled-design-2021-02-10T154651.122.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Several%20journalist%20organisations%20have%20expressed%20strong%20condemnation%20for%20the%20freezing%20of%20NewsClick%E2%80%99s%20accounts%20by%20the%20IT%20department%2C%20depriving%20nearly%20a%20hundred%20media%20professionals%20and%20their%20families%20of%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20salaries%20of%20all%20employees%2C%20including%20support%20staff%2C%20cannot%20be%20disbursed%20including%20for%20the%2019%20days%20of%20work%20in%20December.%20This%20action%20by%20the%20IT%20department%20also%20flouts%20basic%20norms%20of%20natural%20justice%20and%20labour%20laws.%20The%20portal%20has%20maintained%20that%20it%20has%20always%20complied%20with%20tax%20regulations%20and%20that%20there%20was%20no%20basis%20for%20the%20IT%20department%20to%20freeze%20its%20accounts%2C%E2%80%9D%20read%20the%20statement%20issued%20by%20journalist%20organisations%2C%20including%20the%20Indian%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Press%20Corps%20and%20Press%20Club%20of%20India%2C%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20December%2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20follows%20sustained%20harassment%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fenforcement-directorate-newsclick-raids%5C%22%3Eraids%20by%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fnewsclick-it-department-accounts-frozen%5C%22%3EIT%20surveys%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fjournalists-activists-lawyers-express-solidarity-with-newsclick-founder-prabir-purkayastha%5C%22%3Earrest%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20NewsClick%E2%80%99s%20founder%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20and%20its%20HR%20head%20Amit%20Chakraborty%20under%20draconian%20clauses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20been%20observed%20that%20such%20arrests%20of%20mediapersons%20have%20become%20the%20norm%20rather%20than%20the%20exception.%20Both%20continue%20to%20be%20in%20judicial%20custody%20for%20an%20indefinite%20period%20of%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EReproduced%20below%20is%20the%20full%20statement.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJournalist%20bodies%20express%20outrage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%2C%20the%20undersigned%20journalist%20organizations%2C%20deplore%20in%20the%20strongest%20terms%20the%20freezing%20of%20the%20accounts%20of%20the%20web%20news%20portal%20Newsclick.%20This%20move%20by%20the%20IT%20department%20without%20any%20warning%20whatsoever%20has%20in%20one%20stroke%20deprived%20close%20to%20a%20hundred%20media%20persons%20and%20their%20families%20of%20a%20steady%20source%20of%20income.%20The%20salaries%20of%20all%20employees%20including%20support%20staff%20cannot%20be%20disbursed%20including%20for%20the%2019%20days%20of%20work%20in%20December.%20This%20action%20by%20the%20IT%20department%20also%20flouts%20basic%20norms%20of%20natural%20justice%20and%20labor%20laws.%20The%20portal%20has%20maintained%20that%20it%20has%20always%20complied%20with%20tax%20regulations%20and%20that%20there%20was%20no%20basis%20for%20the%20IT%20department%20to%20freeze%20its%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20note%20that%20the%20present%20development%20comes%20on%20the%20heels%20of%20sustained%20harassment%20in%20the%20form%20of%20ED%20raids%20and%20IT%20surveys%20in%202021%20and%20the%20arrest%20of%20NewsClick%E2%80%99s%20founder%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20and%20Administrative%20Officer%20Amit%20Chakraborty%20in%20October%20this%3Cbr%3E%5Cnyear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%2C%20Purkayastha%20and%20Chakraborty%2C%20have%20been%20booked%20under%20draconian%20clauses.%20It%20has%20been%20observed%20that%20such%20arrests%20of%20media%20persons%20have%20become%20the%20norm%20rather%20than%20the%20exception.%20Both%20continue%20to%20be%20in%20judicial%20custody%20for%20an%20indefinite%20period%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20area%20of%20concern%20is%20the%20indiscriminate%20seizure%20of%20electronic%20equipment%2C%20like%20mobile%20phones%20and%20computers%20under%20the%20pretext%20of%20investigations.%20While%20other%20independent%20media%20have%20also%20suffered%20such%20excesses%20with%20equipment%20being%20seized%20and%20confiscated%20for%20months%20altogether%2C%20in%20October%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20electronic%20equipment%20like%20mobile%20phones%20and%20laptops%20of%20Newsclick%20journalists%2C%20ex-employees%20and%20even%20contributors%20was%20seized%20in%20an%20early%20morning%20operation%20which%20was%20unprecedented%20in%20itself.%20Many%2C%20who%20are%20single%20earners%20had%20to%20buy%20new%20equipment%20in%20order%20to%20continue%20working%20as%20there%20was%20no%20assurance%20of%20their%20seized%20equipment%20being%20returned%20in%20a%20definite%20time%20frame%20and%20too%20in%20an%20untampered%20state.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98summoning%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98questioning%E2%80%99%20for%20days%20altogether%20of%20NewsClick%20staff%20and%20reporters%20on%20the%20pretext%20of%20investigation%20has%20been%20another%20mode%20of%20sustained%20harassment%20by%20the%20Special%20Cell%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Police.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20demand%20that%20the%20harassment%20of%20the%20media%20and%20media-persons%20in%20the%20form%20of%20raids%2C%20arrests%20under%20non-bailable%20draconian%20clauses%2C%20freezing%20of%20accounts%20without%20prior%20intimation%20and%20the%20seizure%20of%20electronic%20equipment%20sans%20any%20guidelines%20or%20parameters%20should%20stop%20forthwith.%20As%20such%20equipment%20is%20the%20lifeline%20for%20persons%20operating%20in%20the%20media%20space%2C%20such%20seizures%20effectively%20target%20livelihoods.%20Just%20as%20the%20other%20pillars%20of%20our%20democracy%20need%20to%20be%20allowed%20to%20function%20independently%2C%20so%20does%20the%20media.%20An%20independent%20media%20strengthens%20democracy%3B%20demoralizing%20and%20stifling%20it%20will%20have%20the%20opposite%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20Press%20Club%20of%20India%3Cbr%3E%5Cn2.%20Indian%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Press%20Corps%3Cbr%3E%5Cn3.%20Delhi%20Union%20of%20Journalists%3Cbr%3E%5Cn4.%20Press%20Association%3Cbr%3E%5Cn5.%20Kerala%20Union%20of%20Working%20Journalists%3Cbr%3E%5Cn6.%20The%20Working%20News%20Cameraman%E2%80%99s%20Association%20(WNCA)%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703084454000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F07130338%2FUntitled-design-2021-02-10T154651.122.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fjournalist-organisations-condemn-it-dept-freezing-newsclicks-accounts-say-move-flouts-labour-laws%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'It%20has%20been%20observed%20that%20such%20arrests%20of%20mediapersons%20have%20become%20the%20norm%20rather%20than%20the%20exception%2C'%20read%20the%20statement%20issued%20by%20press%20bodies%2C%20including%20the%20Indian%20Women's%20Press%20Corps%20and%20Press%20Club%20of%20India%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fjournalist-organisations-condemn-it-dept-freezing-newsclicks-accounts-say-move-flouts-labour-laws%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kotak%20Mahindra%20Life%20Insurance%20launch%20TULIP%2C%20combination%20of%20term%2C%20ULIP%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703084289000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-04%2F11%2Ffull%2F1681202727-0555.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcomp