0href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-criticises-centre-for-sitting-over-collegium-proposals-for-judges-transfer-says-it-gives-impression-of-third-party-interferences-218260%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-judges-appointment-gujarat-high-court-242577%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%206%2C%202023%2C%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Sanjay%20Kishan%20Kaul%20and%20Abhay%20S.%20Oka%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-criticises-centre-for-sitting-over-collegium-proposals-for-judges-transfer-says-it-gives-impression-of-third-party-interferences-218260%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Centre%20that%20it%20could%20not%20sit%20on%20transfer%20recommendations%20of%20judges%20as%20it%20sends%20%E2%80%9Ca%20very%20wrong%20signal%E2%80%9D%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthird-party%20interference%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20transferred%20judges%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20repeated%20assertions%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20union%20government%20delayed%20Justice%20Mridul%E2%80%99s%20transfer%2C%20recommended%20on%20July%205%2C%202023%2C%20for%20over%20three%20months%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Funion-govt-appoints-manipur-hc-chief-justice-three-months-after-his-nomination%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclearing%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20on%20October%2016%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20is%20yet%20to%20act%20on%20Justice%20Bhatnagar%E2%80%99s%20transfer%20which%20the%20collegium%20recommended%20on%20August%2010%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20lawyers%20said%20it%20was%20due%20to%20this%20state%20of%20limbo%20that%20the%20special%20bench%20in%20the%20conspiracy%20case%20did%20not%20hear%20arguments%20in%20the%20remaining%20cases%20after%20Justice%20Mridul%E2%80%99s%20transfer%20was%20recommended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9COnce%20both%20the%20judges%20in%20the%20special%20bench%20were%20recommended%20for%20transfer%20in%20July%20and%20August%2C%20there%20was%20uncertainty%20over%20when%20the%20transfers%20would%20actually%20go%20through%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bora%2C%20Fatima%E2%80%99s%20counsel%2C%20told%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EArticle%2014%3Cem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20might%20have%20swayed%20the%20bench%20to%20resist%20hearing%20the%20cases%20after%20July%202023.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20perspective%20of%20ordinary%20litigants%2C%20like%20these%20accused%2C%20delays%20and%20uncertainties%20in%20judicial%20appointments%20and%20transfers%20mean%20long%20periods%20of%20waiting%20to%20have%20meaningful%20hearings%2C%20said%20Bora.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20members%20of%20the%20accused%20were%20hopeful%20that%20the%20new%20bench%20that%20will%20hear%20the%20nine%20cases%20afresh%20will%20deliver%20its%20verdict%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20sure%20we%20will%20get%20justice.%20Everyone%20does%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Saima%2C%20Saleem%E2%80%99s%20daughter.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20let%20it%20not%20come%20so%20late%20that%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20life%20is%20already%20destroyed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESaurav%20Das%20is%20a%20Delhi-based%20investigative%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farticle-14.com%2Fpost%2Fdelayed-justice-alleged-violations-of-constitutional-rights-in-quest-of-9-delhi-riots-accused-for-bail-65825a8f3c539%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20republished%20with%20permission%20from%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.article-14.com%5C%22%3Ewww.article-14.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703080819000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F06130530%2FWhatsApp-Image-2020-07-05-at-1.34.30-PM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdelayed-justice-alleged-violation-constitutional-rights-quest-bail-delhi-riots-accused%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Administrative%20difficulties%20in%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%2C%20scarcity%20of%20time%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20judges%2C%20and%20ground-level%20implications%20of%20a%20larger%20power%20tussle%20between%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20collegium%20have%20together%20resulted%20in%20the%20prolonged%20incarceration%20of%20nine%20accused.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdelayed-justice-alleged-violation-constitutional-rights-quest-bail-delhi-riots-accused%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Centre%20Spent%20Rs%20967.46%20Crore%20During%202019-23%20for%20Publicity%20of%20Govt%20Schemes%20in%20Print%20Media%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F02%2F16132603%2FScreen-Shot-2020-02-16-at-1.25.49-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EBetween%202019-20%20and%202023-24%2C%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20spent%20Rs%20967.46%20crore%20for%20publicity%20of%20its%20schemes%20in%20the%20print%20media.%20The%20advertisements%20were%20routed%20through%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20publicity%20arm%2C%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Communication%20(CBC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20information%20was%20disclosed%20by%20Union%20information%20and%20broadcasting%20minister%2C%20Anurag%20Thakur%2C%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20response%20to%20a%20question%20seeking%20details%20on%20government%20advertisements%20in%20print%20media.%20He%20said%20CBC%20releases%20awareness%2Fpublicity%20campaigns%20through%20print%20media%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.davp.nic.in%2Fwritereaddata%2FFinal_Print_Media_Advt_Policy_Revision_dated_23072020.pdf%5C%22%3EPrint%20Media%20Advertisement%20Policy%2C%202020%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20said%20policy%2C%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Outreach%20and%20Communication%2C%20a%20nodal%20agency%20set%20up%20in%202017%2C%20empanels%20newspapers%20in%20which%20advertisements%20will%20be%20placed.%20A%20newspaper%20should%20have%20a%20minimum%20circulation%20of%202%2C000%20copies%20per%20day%20to%20be%20considered%20eligible%20for%20empanelment.%20The%20policy%20mandates%20that%2080%25%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20newspaper%20advertisements%20be%20reserved%20for%20Indian%20language%20dailies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20details%20of%20expenditure%20incurred%20by%20CBC%2C%20under%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%2C%20on%20awareness%2Fpublicity%20campaigns%20about%20schemes%20and%20programmes%20of%20the%20government%20of%20India%20through%20print%20media%20from%202019-20%20to%202023-24%20(till%2012%20December%202023)%20is%20Rs%20967.46%20crore%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Thakur%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fgovt-spent-rs-96746-crore-on-advertisements-in-print-media-from-2019-20-to-2023-24-2817557%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20news%20agency%20PTI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20data%2C%20there%20were%201%2C19%2C995%20periodicals%2C%20including%20newspapers%2C%20registered%20with%20the%20Registrar%20of%20Newspapers%20for%20India%20(RNI)%20as%20of%20March%2031%2C%202019.%20The%20number%20subsequently%20rose%20to%201%2C43%2C423%20in%202020%2C%201%2C44%2C520%20in%202021%2C%201%2C46%2C045%20in%202022%2C%20and%201%2C48%2C363%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUttar%20Pradesh%20tops%20the%20list%20with%2021%2C660%20periodicals%20registered%20with%20the%20government%2C%20followed%20by%20Maharashtra%20with%2020%2C448%20periodicals%2