f%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Finterventions-in-forex-market-to-curb-excessive-volatility-rbi-to-imf-123122000384_1.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dismissed%20the%20Fund%E2%80%99s%20rationale%20for%20reclassifying%20India%E2%80%99s%20exchange%20rate%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20executive%20director%20at%20IMF%2C%20K.V.%20Subramanian%20and%20senior%20advisors%20Sanjay%20Kumar%20Hansda%20and%20Anand%20Singh%2C%20said%20the%20classification%20is%20%E2%80%9Cincorrect%20and%20inconsistent%20with%20reality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20in%20the%20past%2C%20exchange%20rate%20flexibility%20would%20continue%20to%20be%20the%20first%20line%20of%20defence%20in%20absorbing%20external%20shocks%2C%20with%20interventions%20limited%20to%20addressing%20disorderly%20market%20conditions%2C%20%E2%80%9D%20they%20said%2C%20according%20to%20Business%20Standard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%20has%20always%20claimed%20that%20its%20interventions%20in%20the%20interbank%20market%20which%20determines%20the%20exchange%20rate%20of%20the%20rupee%20is%20to%20curb%20excessive%20volatility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20now%20claimed%20that%20this%20methodology%20follows%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbackward-looking%20statistical%20approach%20that%20relies%20on%20past%20exchange%20rate%20movement%20and%20historical%20data.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMF%20reclassification%20happened%20after%20an%20Article%20IV%20review%20of%20Indian%20policies.%20A%20report%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Feconomy%2Fimf-reclassifies-indias-exchange-rate-regime-to-stabilised-arrangement-due-to-rbis-forex-interventions-11702962330433.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20notes%20that%20this%20consultation%20report%20reviews%20a%20country%E2%80%99s%20current%20and%20medium%20term%20economic%20policies%20and%20outlook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20in%20the%20foreign%20exchange%20market%2C%20where%20the%20Indian%20rupee%20moved%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20narrow%20range%E2%80%9D%20against%20the%20US%20dollar%2C%20the%20movement%20suggested%20that%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cintervention%20likely%20exceeded%20levels%20necessary%20to%20address%20disorderly%20market%20conditions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20reported%20that%20IMF%20has%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20exchange%20interventions%20have%20been%20used%20to%20avoid%20excessive%20volatility%20not%20warranted%20by%20fundamentals.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703073891000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16115416%2Frupee-g803a66102_1920.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fimf-indian-currency-rbi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22RBI's%20'intervention'%20in%20the%20foreign%20exchange%20market%20likely%20exceeded%20levels%20necessary%20to%20address%20disorderly%20market%20conditions%2C%20the%20IMF%20has%20held.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fimf-indian-currency-rbi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22If%20Congress%20Really%20Wants%20to%20Take%20on%20the%20BJP%2C%20Merely%20an%20Electoral%20Battle%20Won't%20Help%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06200522%2FF80eu2gWkAATe66.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20comprehensive%20victories%20registered%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20in%20the%20recent%20assembly%20elections%20of%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Rajasthan%2C%20well-wishers%20of%20the%20Congress%20have%20shown%20surprising%20optimism%20in%20their%20interpretation%20of%20the%20results.%20They%20say%20given%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Congress%20has%20retained%20much%20of%20its%20vote%20shares%20in%20these%20states%2C%20it%20still%20has%20the%20wherewithal%20to%20challenge%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20BJP%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20optimism%2C%20however%2C%20ignores%20the%20current%20predicament%20of%20Indian%20politics%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20challenge%20before%20the%20country%20is%20not%20merely%20electoral.%20It%20is%20a%20more%20serious%20socio-political%20challenge%2C%20and%20merely%20thinking%20of%20it%20in%20terms%20of%20an%20electoral%20solution%20without%20a%20simultaneous%20battle%20for%20the%20soul%20of%20this%20civilisation%20can%20be%20a%20misleading%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20question%20that%20the%20opposition%20forces%20must%20face%20sooner%20or%20later%20is%20whether%20they%20have%20the%20political%20and%20ideological%20strength%20to%20stop%20the%20divisions%20in%20the%20country%20and%20halt%20the%20multiplication%20of%20Hindutva%20votes%20at%20the%20grassroots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27145721%2F404088963_1118521242975440_6389008391481424915_n-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27145721%2F404088963_1118521242975440_6389008391481424915_n-2.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27145721%2F404088963_1118521242975440_6389008391481424915_n-2-300x141.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27145721%2F404088963_1118521242975440_6389008391481424915_n-2-1024x480.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686558%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22563%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20group%20of%20women%20hold%20a%20poster%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20at%20an%20election%20rally%20in%20Rajasthan.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%2FNarendra%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMuslims%20compensate%20for%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20loss%20of%20Hindu%20vote%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20closer%20analysis%20of%20the%20assembly%20elections%20indicates%20that%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20where%20Scheduled%20Caste%20and%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBCs)%20together%20make%20up%20for%20around%2065%25%20of%20the%20population%2C%20Congress%20has%20lost%204%25%20and%206%25%20of%20its%20votes%20among%20these%20communities%20respectively.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20not%20only%20retained%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20the%20SCs%20at%2033%25%2C%20but%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20the%20OBCs%20has%20risen%20by%207%25%20from%2048%25%20to%2055%25.%20It%20has%20also%20increased%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(STs)%20by%209%25%20from%2030%25%20to%2039%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20among%20STs%20has%20also%20increased%20by%2011%25%20as%20compared%20to%202018%2C%20its%20highest%20increase%20of%20votes%20is%20among%20the%20Muslims.%20In%202018%2C%20only%2052%25%20of%20Muslims%20voted%20for%20Congress%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lokniti.org%2Fstate-election-studies%5C%22%3ECSDS-Lokniti%20Post%20Poll%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20this%20time%20around%2085%25%20of%20Muslims%20voted%20for%20it.%20A%20phenomenal%20increase%20of%20around%2033%25%20of%20Muslim%20votes%20is%20the%20single%20most%20reason%20behind%20the%20Congress%20holding%20on%20to%2040.40%25%20votes%20in%20spite%20of%20its%20loss%20of%20votes%20in%20its%20other%20social%20bases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Muslim%20population%20of%20the%20MP%20is%20around%206.5%25%20and%20Congress%20might%20have%20reached%20its%20peak%20share%20among%20the%20Muslim%20community.%20Among%20many%20other%20things%2C%20one%20of%20the%20major%20reasons%20behind%20the%20shift%20of%20OBCs%20and%20Adivasis%20towards%20BJP%20is%20the%20vicious%20Hindutva%20campaign%20by%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20and%20its%20organs%20consistently%20throughout%20the%20year%20without%20any%20political%20challenge.%20This%20will%20be%20amplified%20during%20the%20months%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20resulting%20in%20further%20polarisation%20of%20Hindu%20OBCs%20and%20others.%20The%20INDIA%20bloc%20or%20the%20Congress%20does%20not%20seem%20to%20have%20grassroots%20ideological%20or%20organisational%20counters%20to%20this%20challenge.%20Nor%20do%20they%20seem%20to%20have%20a%20vision%20of%20cultivating%20the%20same%20to%20provide%20an%20alternative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Congress%20obtained%20a%20vote%20share%20of%2043.04%25%20in%202018%2C%20and%20in%202023%2C%20in%20spite%20of%20its%20humiliating%20defeat%2C%20has%20retained%2042.23%25%20of%20the%20vote%20share.%20Thus%2C%20an%20argument%20is%20being%20made%20that%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20social%20base%20is%20intact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20continues%20to%20have%20a%20good%20social%20base%20among%20the%20SCs%20in%20Chhattisgarh%20which%20has%20been%20reflected%20in%20the%20increase%20of%20SC%20votes%20by%206%25%20to%2048%25%20when%20compared%20to%2042%25%20in%202013%20as%20reflected%20in%20the%20CSDS%20analysis.%20But%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20STs%2C%20who%20constitute%2032%25%20of%20the%20state%20population%2C%20has%20decreased%20by%205%25%2C%20from%2047%20to%2042%25%2C%20and%20among%20OBC%20a%20further%20decrease%20of%203%25%2C%20from%2042%20to%2039%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthree-things-bjps-definitive-victory-in-the-assembly-elections-tells-us%5C%22%3EThree%20Things%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Definitive%20Victory%20in%20the%20Assembly%20Elections%20Tells%20Us%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20decline%20in%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20among%20Hindus%20in%20the%20state%20is%20majorly%20compensated%20by%2C%20again%2C%20a%20phenomenal%20increase%20of%20Muslim%20votes%20by%2012%25%20(41%25%20to%2053%25).%20Unlike%20MP%2C%20in%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20increased%20its%20vote%20base%20among%20Muslims%20five-fold%2C%20from%20a%20mere%205%25%20to%2027%25.%20Not%20only%20that%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20increased%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20SCs%20of%20the%20state%20by%2014%25%20%C2%A0(25%25%20to%2039%25)%2C%20among%20the%20STs%20by%2021%25%20(25%25%20to%2046%25)%2C%20and%20among%20OBC%20by%205%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20honour%20of%2040%25%20vote%20share%20of%20the%20Congress%20is%20majorly%20due%20to%20the%20arithmetic%20increase%20of%20votes%20by%20Muslims.%20Unlike%20MP%2C%20it%20is%20not%20saturated%20in%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20but%20BJP%20itself%20has%20become%20a%20strong%20contender%20for%20Muslim%20votes%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Rajasthan%2C%20Congress%20polled%2039.53%25%20votes%2C%20hardly%201.11%25%20less%20than%20in%202018.%20The%20BJP%20has%20increased%20its%20vote%20share%20by%20more%20than%202%25%20to%2041.69%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20what%20the%20CSDS%20survey%20informs%20us%20is%20that%20though%20the%20Congress%20has%20increased%20its%20vote%20share%20by%209%25%20(39%25%20to%2048%25)%20among%20SCs%2C%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20STs%20has%20decreased%20by%206%25%20(41%20to%2035%25)%2C%20and%20among%20OBCs%20a%20decrease%20by%203%25.%20(36%20to%2033%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20its%20vote%20share%20could%20sustain%20its%202018%20figure%2C%20majorly%20because%20the%20Muslim%20vote%20share%20increased%20by%20an%20astounding%2028%25%20(62%25%20in%202018%20to%2090%25%20in%202023).%20The%20emergence%20of%20an%20independent%20Adivasi%20party%20has%20cut%20into%20the%20ST%20vote%20share%20of%20both%20BJP%20and%20Congress.%20But%20the%20BJP%20almost%20retained%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20the%20SCs%20at%2033%25%20and%20increased%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20the%20OBC%20by%205%25%2C%20when%20compared%20to%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20loss%20of%203%25%20vote%20share%20of%20OBC%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20phenomenal%20increase%20of%20Muslim%20votes%20for%20the%20Congress%20by%2012%25-31%25%20in%20the%20three%20states%20could%20compensate%20for%20its%20loss%20of%20votes%20among%20its%20traditional%20Hindu%20vote%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20survey%20also%20suggests%20that%20among%20the%20Hindus%2C%20especially%20SC%2C%20ST%2C%20and%20OBCs%2C%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20has%20either%20stagnated%20or%20sharply%20decreased.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20increased%20its%20Hindu%20vote%20share%20by%2016%20to%2034%25%20by%20encroaching%20upon%20the%20Congress%20social%20base%20of%20the%20SCs%2C%20STS%2C%20and%20OBCs.%20It%20is%20also%20reflected%20in%20the%20depleting%20vote%20share%20of%20the%20smaller%20parties%20in%20the%20fray%2C%20much%20to%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeing%20a%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20political%20replica%20won%E2%80%99t%20help%20Congress%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20polarisation%20is%20ominous%20for%20the%202024%20elections.%20Even%20among%20the%20rural-urban%2C%20male-female%2C%20and%20other%20class%20categories%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20made%20significant%20inroads%2C%20with%20its%20twin%20agenda%20of%20communal%20polarisation%20and%20last-minute%20personalised%20welfare%20dole-outs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20it%20is%20already%20obvious%20that%20BJP-RSS%20is%20pitching%20on%20issues%20like%20national%20security%2C%20Ram%20Mandir%2C%20pride%20of%20Hindu%20Rashtra%2C%20and%20such%20mythical%20and%20emotive%20agendas%20to%20which%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%E2%80%99s%20counters%20are%20either%20collusive%20or%20complementary%20instead%20of%20confronting%20with%20alternate%20vision%20and%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20electoral%20data%20of%20the%20recent%20assembly%20elections%20has%20many%20political%20and%20ideological%20lessons.%20It%20would%20be%20self-deception%20to%20take%20comfort%20in%20the%20vulnerable%20vote%20share%20of%20the%20Congress%20and%20dream%20of%20a%20miracle%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20high%20chances%20that%20in%20a%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20fought%20on%20hyper-religious%20nationalism%2C%20the%20very%20same%20Congress%20votes%20may%20shift%20to%20the%20BJP.%20The%20battle%20of%202024%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20not%20a%20mathematical%20calculation%20for%20the%20opposition%2C%20and%20surely%20cannot%20be%20won%20by%20diluting%20the%20secular%20agenda%20or%20becoming%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20political%20replica.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20BJP-RSS%20is%20fighting%20an%20ideological%20and%20political%20battle%20against%20the%20Indian%20Republic%2C%20of%20which%20electoral%20victories%20are%20one%20among%20the%20many%20strategies%2C%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%2C%20including%20the%20Congress%20and%20its%20supporters%2C%20cannot%20dream%20of%20saving%20the%20idea%20of%20India%20by%20staging%20an%20unprincipled%20electoral%20battle%20with%20the%20diluted%20versions%20of%20the%20same%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESerious%20politics%20demand%20imagination%20and%20preparation%20beyond%202024%20and%20the%20electoral%20arena%20with%20an%20agenda%20and%20vision%20for%20a%20battle%20for%20substantive%20equality%2C%20social-economic%20justice%20and%20fraternity%2C%20and%20not%20a%20diluted%20version%20of%20Hindutva.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fshivasundar%5C%22%3EShivasundar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20activist%20and%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20based%20in%20Bangalore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703073623000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06200522%2FF80eu2gWkAATe66.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcongress-take-on-bjp-mere-electoral-battle-not-enough%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Since%20the%20assembly%20election%20results%2C%20many%20have%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20vote%20share%20of%20the%20Congress%20has%20been%20intact%20despite%20its%20defeats.%20What%20they%20miss%20is%20the%20steep%20fall%20in%20the%20traditional%20Hindu%20vote%20base%20of%20the%20Congress%20is%20compensated%20by%20an%20increase%20in%20its%20Muslim%20vote%20share.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcongress-take-on-bjp-mere-electoral-battle-not-enough%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ireland%20brings%20legal%20action%20against%20UK%20under%20European%20Convention%20on%20Human%20Rights%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703073600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F70x70%2Fskynews-micheal-martin-ireland_6399232.jpg%3F20231220135908%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Firish-government-launches-legal-challenge-against-uks-controversial-northern-ireland-legacy-bill-13034806%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Irish%20government%20is%20to%20bring%20a%20legal%20case%20against%20the%20UK%20under%20the%20European%20Convention%20on%20Human%20Rights%20(ECHR).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A175%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Firish-government-launches-legal-challenge-against-uks-controversial-northern-ireland-legacy-bill-13034806%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Firish-government-launches-legal-challenge-against-uks-controversial-northern-ireland-legacy-bill-13034806%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Firish-government-launches-legal-challenge-against-uks-controversial-northern-ireland-legacy-bill-13034806%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Due%20to%20Cost%20and%20Time%20Concerns%2C%20Silkyara%20Tunnel%20Project%20Said%20No%20to%20Separate%20Escape%20Tunnel%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01140335%2FGACaXNpbYAASMBx.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Last%20month%2C%2041%20workers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcollapses-during-silkyara-tunnel-construction-central-team%5C%22%3Ewere%20trapped%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Silkyara-Barkot%20tunnel%20in%20Uttarakhand%20for%2017%20days.%20A%20late%20environmental%20impact%20assessment%20(EIA)%20report%2C%20reviewed%20by%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20Indian%20Express%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20revealed%20that%20the%20situation%20might%20have%20been%20avoided%20if%20the%20option%20of%20a%20separate%20escape%20tunnel%20had%20not%20been%20ruled%20out%20due%20to%20cost%20and%20time%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20weighing%20options%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbest-suited%20cross-section%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20tunnel%2C%20the%20EIA%20report%20rejected%20%E2%80%93%20as%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20recommended%20at%20all%20and%20ignored%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20a%20%E2%80%9Cseparation%20wall%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20tunnel%E2%80%99s%20carriageway%20along%20with%20%E2%80%9Cegress%20openings%E2%80%9D%20for%20%E2%80%9Cescape%E2%80%9D%20during%20an%20emergency%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20instead%20recommended%20the%20original%20project%20plan%3A%20A%20dedicated%203.5m%20escape%20channel%20separated%20by%20a%20concrete%20barrier%20from%20a%207m%20carriageway%20meant%20for%20two-way%20traffic%20inside%20a%20D-shaped%20tunnel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20this%20design%20was%20later%20modified%20during%20the%20construction%2C%20apparently%20for%20better%20space%20utilisation%20and%20traffic%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInstead%20of%20leaving%20an%20escape%20channel%20on%20the%20left%2C%20we%20put%20the%20divider%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20tunnel%20for%20single-way%20traffic%20on%20either%20side.%20This%20created%20more%20space%20for%20traffic%20and%20eliminated%20the%20risk%20of%20head-on%20collisions%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20senior%20project%20engineer%20told%20the%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20tunnelling%20expert%20involved%20in%20the%20rescue%20operation%20last%20month%20pointed%20out%20that%20a%20total%20blockage%20of%20the%20Silkyara%20tunnel%20made%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20positioning%20of%20the%20divider%E2%80%9D%20immaterial%20and%20only%20a%20separate%20evacuation%20tunnel%20could%20have%20helped.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20situation%20like%20this%20(collapse)%20requires%20a%20separate%20evacuation%20duct%20running%20next%20to%20the%20main%20tunnel%20with%20access%20at%20regular%20intervals%2C%20or%20a%20few%20lateral%20inclined%20escape%20adits%20rising%20to%20the%20ground%20surface.%20Having%20an%20escape%20passage%20in%20the%20same%20tunnel%20helps%20during%20traffic%20or%20fire%20incidents%2C%20but%20not%20if%20there%20is%20a%20total%20blockage%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20expert%20told%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20construction%20time%20and%20cost%20required%20is%20more%20for%20two%20tunnels%2C%20two%20portals%20and%20two%20sets%20of%20ventilation%20systems.%20This%20system%20is%20best%20suited%20in%20case%20of%20heavy%20traffic%20volume%20but%20at%20current%20location%2C%20the%20traffic%20volume%20is%20only%202000%20PCU%20(passenger%20car%20units).%20Hence%20this%20proposal%20is%20also%20not%20recommended%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20EIA%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Futtarakhand-tunnel-collapse-warning-environment-development%5C%22%3EIf%20Lessons%20Are%20Not%20Learnt%2C%20Expect%20More%20Silkyaras%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20Road%20Transport%20and%20Highways%20submitted%20the%20208-page%20rapid%20EIA%20report%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20September%202020.%20By%20then%2C%20the%20Silkyara%20tunnel%20was%20%E2%80%9Calready%20under%20construction%20and%20more%20than%2015%25%20of%20the%20work%20has%20already%20been%20completed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20work%20was%20already%20on%2C%20the%20rapid%20EIA%20report%20reflected%20the%20project%20plan.%20For%20the%20rescue%20channel%2C%20too%2C%20it%20rejected%20the%20options%20not%20on%20the%20card.%20It%20could%20not%20have%20predicted%20that%20the%20project%20would%20go%20on%20to%20drop%20the%20escape%20channel%20altogether%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20consultant%20involved%20in%20the%20EIA%20process%20told%20the%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Silkyara-Barkot%20tunnel%20is%20part%20of%20the%20889-km%20Char%20Dham%20project.%20The%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party-led%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%C2%A0%20government%20split%20the%20project%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fchar-dham-highway-project-shouldve-undergone-impact-assessment-v-k-saraswat%5C%22%3E53%20separate%20sections%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20none%20over%20100%20kilometre%20in%20length%2C%20and%20evaded%20the%20need%20for%20an%20environmental%20impact%20assessment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20the%20Congress-led%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance%20had%20decided%20to%20waive%20environmental%20clearances%20for%20road%20projects%20less%20than%20100%20km%20long.%20Three%20years%20later%2C%20the%20NDA%20made%20use%20of%20this%20waiver.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703071835000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01140335%2FGACaXNpbYAASMBx.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fdue-to-cost-and-time-concerns-silkyara-tunnel-project-said-no-to-separate-escape-tunnel-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20late%20environmental%20impact%20assessment%20report%2C%20reviewed%20by%20the%20'Indian%20Express'%2C%20revealed%20that%20the%20situation%20%E2%80%93%20where%2041%20workers%20were%20trapped%20in%20the%20tunnel%20for%2017%20days%20%E2%80%93%20might%20have%20been%20avoided%20if%20the%20option%20of%20a%20separate%20escape%20tunnel%20had%20not%20been%20ruled%20out.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fdue-to-cost-and-time-concerns-silkyara-tunnel-project-said-no-to-separate-escape-tunnel-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UN%20Security%20Council%20vote%20on%20Gaza%20aid%20delayed%20again%20over%20US%20talks%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703071800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-israel-gaza_6399019.jpg%3F20231220103445%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fun-security-council-vote-on-gaza-aid-delayed-again-over-talks-with-us-on-ceasefire-13034723%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20UN%20Security%20Council%20vote%20on%20a%20resolution%20to%20increase%20much-needed%20aid%20deliveries%20to%20Gaza%20has%20been%20delayed%20as%20talks%20continue%20to%20avoid%20a%20third%20US%20veto%20over%20a%20halt%20in%20the%20fighting%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A413%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fun-security-council-vote-on-gaza-aid-delayed-again-over-talks-with-us-on-ceasefire-13034723%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fun-security-council-vote-on-gaza-aid-delayed-again-over-talks-with-us-on-ceasefire-13034723%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fun-security-council-vote-on-gaza-aid-delayed-again-over-talks-with-us-on-ceasefire-13034723%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Onion%20Export%20Ban%20Worsens%20Farmer%20Distress%2C%26nbsp%3BCould%20Cost%20India%20Its%20Overseas%20Market%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12135301%2FOnions.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20After%20the%20price%20of%20onions%20skyrocketed%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20neighbouring%20countries%20following%20an%20export%20ban%20on%20the%20vegetable%20in%20India%2C%20questions%20have%20been%20raised%20on%20if%20India%20is%20losing%20an%20established%20international%20market%20for%20its%20produce%20as%20Nepal%20and%20others%20begin%20assessing%20alternatives%20to%20the%20Indian%20onion.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20farmers%20who%20grew%20the%20crop%20expecting%20profits%20are%20consumed%20with%20worry%20due%20to%20falling%20domestic%20prices.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20had%20introduced%20a%20minimum%20export%20price%20of%20%24800%20per%20tonne%20on%20onion%20exports%20on%20October%2028%20this%20year.%20On%20December%208%2C%20the%20curbs%20on%20onion%20export%20were%20extended%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20total%20ban%20until%20March%2031%2C%202024.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20sweeping%20export%20ban%2C%20people%20in%20Nepal%20are%20grappling%20with%20a%20shortage%20of%20the%20kitchen%20staple.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Nepal%20government%20has%20announced%20its%20decision%20to%20formally%20request%20India%20to%20send%20onions%20to%20address%20the%20scarcity%20that%20has%20affected%20markets%20in%20the%20country%20after%20onion%20importers%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20a%20potential%20shortage%20of%20the%20vegetable%20in%20Nepal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20per%20the%20request%20by%20onion%20traders%2C%20we%20have%20decided%20to%20request%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20send%20onion%20to%20Nepal.%20We%20will%20send%20the%20request%20soon%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20official%20in%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20industry%20ministry%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fmoney%2F2023%2F12%2F18%2Fnepal-to-request-india-for-onion-supply%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etold%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20%3Cem%3EKathmandu%20Post.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENepal%20relies%20almost%20exclusively%20on%20India%20for%20all%20of%20its%20onion%20imports.%20Any%20ripples%20in%20onion%20supply%20from%20India%20have%20an%20amplified%20impact%20on%20Nepali%20markets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Findias-onion-export-ban-hits-neighbouring-countries-steep-price-hikes-reported%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Onion%20Export%20Ban%20Hits%20Neighbouring%20Countries%2C%20Steep%20Price%20Hikes%20Reported%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELosing%20international%20market%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20directive%2C%20the%20export%20of%20onions%20may%20be%20allowed%20based%20on%20permission%20granted%20by%20the%20government%20of%20India%20to%20other%20countries%20based%20on%20the%20request%20of%20their%20governments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Nepali%20officials%20are%20also%20in%20discussions%20with%20onion%20importers%20to%20potentially%20source%20the%20vegetable%20from%20other%20countries%20like%20Pakistan%20and%20China.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EImporting%20large%20quantities%20of%20onion%20from%20other%20countries%2C%20other%20than%20India%2C%20is%20not%20possible%20because%20it%20is%20a%20perishable%20commodity%2C%20said%20the%20government%20officials.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20no%20government%20bodies%20import%20onions%2C%20our%20role%20is%20to%20facilitate%20the%20importers%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fmoney%2F2023%2F12%2F18%2Fnepal-to-request-india-for-onion-supply%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20officials.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20if%20it%20takes%20time%20to%20get%20the%20approval%20from%20the%20Indian%20government%2C%20we%20have%20an%20option%20to%20import%20from%20third%20countries%2C%20including%20China%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20may%20be%20noted%20that%20in%20the%20last%20fiscal%20year%2C%20Nepal%20imported%20around%20190%20tonnes%20of%20onions%20worth%20Rs%206.75%20billion%20from%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ban%20has%20also%20led%20to%20onion%20smuggling%20across%20the%20porous%20borders%20with%20law%20enforcement%20seizing%20illegally%20imported%20onions%20on%20several%20occasions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDomestic%20impact%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20export%20ban%20has%20not%20only%20affected%20the%20price%20of%20onions%20internationally%2C%20but%20has%20also%20caused%20a%20price%20drop%20in%20the%20domestic%20market%20affecting%20farmer%20incomes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHundreds%20of%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fnashik%2Fonion-farmers-protest-on-mumbai-agra-highway-over-centres-ban-on-exports%2Farticleshow%2F105837748.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20onion%20farmers%20in%20Maharashtra%E2%80%99s%20Nashik%20district%20blocked%20the%20Mumbai-Agra%20Highway%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20at%20three%20locations%20last%20week%20in%20protest%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20ban%20the%20export%20of%20onions%2C%20%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOngoing%20protests%20at%20onion%20markets%20in%20Lasalgaon%2C%20Nandgaon%2C%20Pimpalgaon%2C%20and%20Umarane%20in%20Nashik%20had%20led%20to%20temporary%20closure%20of%20operations%20in%20these%20areas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20imposition%20of%20MEP%20in%20October%2C%20the%20average%20wholesale%20prices%20of%20onions%20had%20dropped%20by%2024%25%20in%20the%20first%20five%20days%20to%20Rs%203%2C650%20per%20quintal%20at%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20largest%20wholesale%20onion%20market%20at%20Lasalgaon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaharashtra%E2%80%99s%20deputy%20chief%20ministers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fpune%2Fonion-export-ban-devendra-fadnavis-ajit-pawar-delhi-meet-amit-shah-9072576%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSenior%2520Maharashtra%2520ministers%252C%2520including%2520Deputy%2Ctotal%2520ban%2520on%2520onion%2520exports.%5C%22%3EAjit%20Pawar%20and%20Devendra%20Fadnavis%20rushed%20to%20New%20Delhi%20to%20meet%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday%20to%20discuss%20a%20possible%20way%20out%20of%20the%20total%20ban%20on%20onion%20exports%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%20The%20delegation%20might%20also%20include%20food%20and%20civil%20supplies%20minister%20Chhagan%20Bhujbal%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaharashtra%20chief%20minister%20Eknath%20Shinde%20also%20had%20a%20telephonic%20conversation%20with%20Union%20consumers%20affairs%20minister%20Piyush%20Goyal%20on%20the%20issue.%C2%A0%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20find%20out%20a%20way%20so%20that%20farmers%20and%20customers%20do%20not%20face%20losses%20due%20to%20the%20ban%20on%20export%20of%20onions%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fwill-find-way-to-ensure-farmers-dont-face-losses-due-to-onion-export-ban-maharashtra-chief-minister-eknath-shinde%2Fcid%2F1986066%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20Shinde%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20government%20is%20under%20significant%20pressure%20to%20alleviate%20the%20plight%20of%20farmers%20affected%20by%20the%20Union%E2%80%99s%20ban%20as%20the%20opposition%20also%20scaled%20up%20its%20attack%20on%20this%20front%2C%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fmaharashtra%2Fonion-politics-heats-up-maharashtra-as-bjp-ncp-spar-over-price-rise-2656859%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnion%20farmers%20in%20Karnataka%20are%20also%20facing%20a%20significant%20economic%20setback%20as%20onion%20prices%20took%20a%20nosedive%20following%20the%20export%20ban.%20Farmers%20who%20managed%20to%20grow%20the%20crop%20despite%20drought%20conditions%20in%20Karnataka%20are%20now%20worried%20if%20they%20will%20get%20a%20good%20price%20for%20the%20produce.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EN.M.%20Siddesh%2C%20president%20of%20the%20state%20onion%20farmers%E2%80%99%20association%2C%20said%20that%20medium-quality%20onions%20were%20priced%20between%20Rs%204%2C500%20and%20Rs%206%2C000%20per%20quintal%2C%20with%20good%20quality%20onions%20fetching%20Rs%207%2C000%20to%20Rs%208%2C000%20per%20quintal%20before%20the%20ban.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20now%20the%20prices%20have%20come%20down%20to%20Rs%20800%20to%201%2C200%20and%20Rs%202%2C000%20to%202%2C500%20for%20medium%20to%20good%20quality%20onions%20respectively.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20now%20planning%20to%20launch%20a%20massive%20protest%20against%20the%20crash%20in%20onion%20prices%2C%20demanding%20the%20government%20to%20lift%20the%20ban.%20We%20will%20soon%20hold%20a%20massive%20protest%20in%20Gadag%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhubballi%2Fworries-mount-as-onion-prices-drop-after-centres-export-ban%2Farticleshow%2F106056450.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Salim%20Byhatti%2C%20president%20of%20the%20onion%2Fpotato%20merchants%20association%2C%20APMC%2C%20Hubballi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnion%20farmers%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhubballi%2Fworries-mount-as-onion-prices-drop-after-centres-export-ban%2Farticleshow%2F106056450.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eurged%20the%20government%20to%20announce%20a%20minimum%20support%20price%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20onions%20and%20lift%20the%20export%20ban%20to%20protect%20farmers%20from%20further%20losses.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703070033000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12135301%2FOnions.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Fonion-export-ban-worsens-farmer-distress-could-cost-india-its-overseas-market%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Questions%20have%20been%20raised%20on%20if%20India%20is%20losing%20an%20established%20international%20market%20for%20its%20onions%20as%20Nepal%20and%20others%20begin%20assessing%20alternatives%20to%20the%20Indian%20onion.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Fonion-export-ban-worsens-farmer-distress-could-cost-india-its-overseas-market%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Telecom%20Bill%202023%20Is%20a%20Repackaged%20Version%20of%20the%20Archaic%20Colonial%20Law%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20154844%2Fsunset-5423633_1280.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Telecommunications%20Bill%2C%202023%20(%E2%80%9CTelecom%20Bill%2C%202023%E2%80%9D)%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20December%2018%2C%20almost%20a%20year%20after%20the%20conclusion%20of%20the%20consultation%20process%20for%20its%202022%20counterpart%2C%20i.e.%20the%20draft%20Indian%20Telecommunication%20Bill%2C%202022%20(%E2%80%9CTelecom%20Bill%2C%202022%E2%80%9D).%20After%20several%20reported%20inter-ministerial%20discussions%20over%20the%20year%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Telecommunications%20(%E2%80%9CDoT%E2%80%9D)%20has%20released%20a%20repackaged%20version%20of%20the%20colonial%201885%20law%20it%20meant%20to%20overhaul%2C%20which%20continues%20to%20retain%20the%20draconian%20surveillance%20and%20internet%20suspension%20powers%20of%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20should%20you%20care%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELaws%20governing%20telecommunication%20services%20in%20the%20country%20have%20historically%20been%20used%20and%20misused%20to%20surveil%20our%20devices%20and%20suspend%20our%20internet.%20With%20changing%20times%2C%20these%20laws%20are%20also%20evolving%2C%20expanding%20the%20scope%20of%20applicability%20to%20new%20and%20emerging%20services.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1tX5sTSZEgo-9b3fVoInXFlUY93ZlFcYj%2Fview%3Fref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3ETelecom%20Bill%2C%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%20attempted%20to%20include%20online%20communication%20services%20(Signal%2C%20Zoom%2C%20Skype%2C%20Gmail)%20under%20the%20licensing%20regime%20historically%20applicable%20to%20broadcasting%20services.%20The%20expansion%20of%20surveillance%20and%20suspension%20powers%20from%20traditional%20broadcasting%20services%20to%20online%20communication%20services%20will%20cause%20irreparable%20damage%20to%20user%20rights%20and%20democratic%20freedoms.%C2%A0%20Definitional%20ambiguity%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1U56m1jE8CsLH7GMl5DTOu3iA4TxOito8%2Fview%3Fusp%3Dsharing%5C%22%3ETelecom%20Bill%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20leaves%20us%20worried%20and%20confused%20about%20its%20application%20to%20internet%20services.%20In%20any%20scenario%2C%20the%20bill%20will%20have%20implications%20for%20our%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy%20as%20well%20as%20our%20constitutional%20freedoms%20such%20as%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20right%20to%20receive%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20journey%20of%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%20from%202022%20till%202023%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%20was%20released%20for%20public%20consultation%20on%20September%2021%2C%202022%2C%C2%A0%20following%20the%20release%20of%20the%20consultation%20paper%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9CNeed%20for%20a%20new%20legal%20framework%20governing%20Telecommunication%20in%20India%E2%80%9D%20which%20was%20published%20on%20July%2023%2C%202022.%20Interestingly%2C%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%2C%20which%20was%20released%20merely%20three%20weeks%20after%20the%20conclusion%20of%20the%20consultation%20period%20for%20the%20paper%2C%20inserted%20controversial%20provisions%2C%20which%20was%20not%20present%20in%20the%20latter.%20In%20a%20response%20to%20a%20Right%20to%20Information%20(%E2%80%9CRTI%E2%80%9D)%20filed%20by%20us%2C%20the%20DoT%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1cRUKSbOO0lzpy6ohWTKhBzCl-ezSG40H%2Fview%3Fusp%3Dshare_link%26ref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3Eshared%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20responses%20it%20received%20on%20the%20consultation%20paper%20%5BRead%20our%20comments%20on%20the%20paper%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.internetfreedom.in%2Fcomments-on-the-consultation-paper-on-the%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%5D.%20The%20DoT%20however%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fhttps-internetfreedom-in-digital-transparency-report-for-january-2023%2F%5C%22%3Erefused%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20share%20the%20comments%20it%20received%20on%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%2C%20which%20were%20invited%20till%20late%20last%20year%20%5BRead%20our%20comments%20on%20the%20paper%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Four-response-to-the-draft-telecom-bill-2022%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%5D.%20The%20absence%20of%20such%20disclosures%20make%20the%20reasoning%2Finspiration%20behind%20the%20changes%20non-transparent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKey%20concerns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERepackaged%20control%2C%20replicated%20language%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98statement%20of%20objects%20and%20reasons%E2%80%99%20under%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20acknowledges%20the%20need%20to%20create%20a%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9Clegal%20and%20regulatory%20framework%20that%20focuses%20on%20safe%20and%20secure%20telecommunication%20network%20that%20provides%20for%20digitally%20inclusive%20growth%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D.%20According%20to%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%2C%20the%20aim%20of%20introducing%20such%20a%20bill%20was%20to%20%E2%80%8B%E2%80%8Bcreate%20a%20modern%20and%20future-ready%20comprehensive%20framework%20for%20the%20telecommunication%20sector%20in%20India%20which%20is%20currently%20governed%20by%20several%20colonial%20laws.%20While%20we%20agree%20with%20the%20need%20to%20reform%20the%20laws%20governing%20the%20sector%2C%20we%20dispute%20the%20approach%20adopted%20by%20the%20DoT%20to%20do%20so.%20Key%20provisions%20relating%20to%20surveillance%20and%20internet%20suspension%2C%20which%20have%20a%20long%20lasting%2C%20profound%20impact%20on%20our%20digital%20rights%2C%20have%20been%20replicated%20verbatim%20from%20the%20Telegraph%20Act%20of%201885.%20It%20will%20be%20unfair%20to%20say%20that%20the%20bill%20has%20not%20undergone%20changes%20in%20phrasing%2C%20but%20it%20will%20also%20be%20unfair%20to%20equate%20this%20change%20with%20reform.%20A%20contested%20provision%20of%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%2C%20i.e.%20licensing%2C%20has%20been%20replaced%2C%20only%20in%20name%2C%20by%20a%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%9Cauthorisation%E2%80%9D.%20The%20fundamental%20function%20of%20issuing%20authorisation%20is%20still%20an%20exclusive%20right%20of%20the%20Union%20government.%20Reliance%20on%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20safety%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20security%E2%80%9D%20grounds%20to%20empower%20the%20Union%20government%20with%20powers%20to%20temporarily%20possess%2C%20suspend%2C%20intercept%2C%20detain%20any%20telecommunication%20service%20or%20telecommunication%20network%20from%20an%20authorised%20entity%20is%20nothing%20more%20than%20an%20old%20trick%20of%20the%201885%20playbook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAmbiguity%20around%20fundamental%20concepts%20of%20scope%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20backlash%20received%20by%20the%20DoT%20during%20the%20public%20consultation%20on%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%20was%20around%20the%20wide%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%98telecommunication%20services%E2%80%99%20which%20explicitly%20included%20a%20long%20list%20of%20online%20communication%20services.%20The%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%98telecommunication%E2%80%99%20%5BClause%202(p)%5D%20read%20with%20%E2%80%98telecommunication%20services%E2%80%99%20%5BClause%202(t)%5D%20is%20now%20heavily%20diluted%20and%20truncated%2C%20creating%20uncertainty%20about%20the%20scope%20of%20applicability%20to%20internet%20services.%20Without%20this%20clarity%2C%20it%20creates%20hindrances%20in%20foreseeing%20the%20impact%20on%20user%20rights%20and%20thus%20meaningfully%20responding%20to%20or%20analysing%20the%20bill.%20Such%20definitional%20ambiguity%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20intentional%2C%20leaves%20the%20scope%20wide%20enough%20for%20online%20communication%20services%20to%20be%20included%20within%20its%20ambit.%20If%20internet%20services%20are%20included%20in%20the%20law%E2%80%99s%20ambit%2C%20then%20the%20several%20alarming%20requirements%20related%20to%20surveillance%2C%20possession%2C%20suspension%2C%20authorisation%2C%20etc.%20will%20be%20applied%20to%20those%20services%20as%20well%2C%20deepening%20the%20threats%20to%20our%20rights%20and%20freedoms.%20To%20avoid%20expansion%20or%20re-interpretation%20of%20the%20scope%20in%20the%20future%2C%20the%20definition%20of%20telecommunication%20and%20telecommunication%20services%2C%20in%20the%20bill%20itself%2C%20must%20explicitly%20exclude%20internet%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThreats%20to%20user%20privacy%20and%20rights%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20deteriorates%20user%20rights%20in%20several%20other%20ways%2C%20many%20of%20which%20directly%20infringe%20on%20the%20user%E2%80%99s%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy.%20Clause%203(7)%20is%20one%20such%20privacy%20invading%20provision%20which%20imposes%20an%20obligation%20on%20any%20authorised%20entity%2C%20as%20notified%20by%20the%20Union%20govt%2C%20to%20identify%20the%20person%20to%20whom%20it%20provides%20telecom%20services%2C%20through%20use%20of%20any%20verifiable%20biometric%20based%20identification%20%E2%80%9Cas%20may%20be%20prescribed%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%201885%20also%20contained%20a%20similar%20provision%20for%20licensed%20entities%2C%20but%20with%20safeguards%20and%20specificity.%20Section%204(3)(a)%20listed%20the%20various%20modes%20of%20authentication%20that%20may%20be%20used%20by%20the%20licensee%2C%20including%20offline%20authentication%2C%20and%20also%20explicitly%20mentioned%20alternatives%20authentication%20modes%20to%20Aadhaar%20such%20as%20passport.%20The%20%E2%80%9Cbiometric%E2%80%9D%20based%20identification%20mode%20did%20not%20even%20feature%20in%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022.%20This%20inclusion%20of%20%E2%80%9Cverifiable%20biometric%20based%20identification%E2%80%9D%20raises%20fears%20that%20it%20may%20provide%20a%20legislative%20basis%20for%20the%20mandatory%20linking%20of%20Aadhaar%20to%20mobile%20phones%20which%20was%20ruled%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Faadhaar-verdict-supreme-court-judgment-uidai-5374829%2F%5C%22%3Eunconstitutional%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India.%20Thus%2C%20this%20provision%20is%20bereft%20of%20safeguards%20on%20many%20levels%2C%20but%20is%20most%20prominently%20inadequate%20for%20pushing%20technology%20solutions%20for%20a%20country%20which%20is%20still%20largely%20not%20digital%20literate.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20informed%20understanding%20of%20how%20such%20biometric%20data%20will%20be%20used%2C%20stored%2C%20processed%2C%20and%20shared%20among%20majority%20of%20the%20public%2C%20and%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20non-robust%20data%20protection%20act%20which%20provides%20wise%20ranging%20exemptions%20to%20the%20government%2C%20such%20technology%20should%20not%20be%20adopted%20for%20a%20routine%20procedure%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20offline%20alternative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20potentially%20privacy%20infringing%20provision%20is%20Clause%2029%20of%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20which%20imposes%20a%20duty%20on%20users%20to%20not%20furnish%20any%20false%20information%20while%20establishing%20their%20identity%20for%20availing%20%E2%80%98telecommunication%20services%E2%80%99.%20If%20applicable%20to%20internet%20services%2C%20the%20ambiguous%20phrasing%20of%20Clause%203(7)%20and%2029%20will%20have%20damaging%20consequences%20for%20a%20user%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20stay%20anonymous%20while%20communicating.%20This%20can%20have%20a%20deleterious%20impact%20on%20vulnerable%20individuals%20such%20as%20whistleblowers%20and%20journalists%2C%20who%20wish%20to%20keep%20their%20identity%20anonymous.%20Services%20such%20as%20Twitter%20and%20Instagram%2C%20which%20currently%20provide%20users%20with%20the%20option%20to%20communicate%20anonymously%2C%20will%20possibly%20have%20to%20take%20back%20this%20facility%20if%20they%20wish%20to%20operate%20in%20India.%20The%20application%20of%20this%20clause%20in%20the%20context%20of%20traditional%20telecommunication%20services%20can%20be%20viewed%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20rising%20cybercrime%20in%20the%20country.%20Notably%2C%20the%20associated%20penalty%20for%20failing%20to%20comply%20with%20these%20provisions%20are%2C%20i.e.%20up%20to%20INR%2025%2C000%20for%20the%20first%20offence%20and%20for%20the%20second%20or%20subsequent%20offences%2C%20up%20to%20INR%2050%2C000%20for%20every%20day%20till%20the%20contravention%20continues.%20The%20imposition%20of%20such%20hefty%20fines%20must%20be%20avoided%20for%20such%20clauses%20given%20the%20low%20digital%20literacy%20rates%20in%20the%20country%20as%20well%20as%20to%20avoid%20the%20misuse%20of%20the%20associated%20penalty%20by%20authorities%2C%20to%20coerce%20users%20into%20mandatorily%20using%20Aadhaar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Telecommunications%20Bill%20Lays%20the%20Ground%20for%20Totalitarian%20Control%20of%20the%20Internet%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Ftelecommunications-bill-lays-the-ground-for-totalitarian-control-of-the-internet%5C%22%3ETelecommunications%20Bill%20Lays%20the%20Ground%20for%20Totalitarian%20Control%20of%20the%20Internet%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECentralised%20executive%20control%20and%20powers%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ability%20to%20suspend%2C%20curtail%2C%20or%20revoke%20the%20authorisation%20or%20assignment%20in%20case%20of%20breach%20of%20any%20of%20its%20terms%20and%20conditions%20rests%20with%20the%20Union%20government%20%5BClause%2032(2)%5D.%20A%20similar%20provision%20to%20revoke%20the%20licence%20exists%20in%20the%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%201885%2C%20but%20it%20does%20not%20have%20any%20provisions%20for%20suspension%20of%20the%20licence.%20The%20entirety%20of%20Clause%2020%20in%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20temporarily%20possess%2C%20suspend%2C%20intercept%2C%20detain%20any%20telecommunication%20service%20%5B20(1)(a)%5D%2C%20to%20intercept%2C%20detain%2C%20disclose%2C%20or%20suspend%20any%20message%20or%20class%20of%20messages%20%5B20(2)(a)%5D%2C%20to%20direct%20suspension%20of%20any%20telecommunication%20service%20or%20class%20of%20telecommunication%20%5B20(2)(b)%5D%2C%20or%20to%20notify%20encryption%20and%20data%20processing%20standards%20%5B19(f)%5D%2C%20cements%20the%20colonial%20powers%20of%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20which%20upon%20misused%20and%20if%20extended%20to%20internet%20services%2C%20may%20become%20nothing%20less%20than%20draconian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClause%2022(3)%20read%20with%202(f)%20empowers%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20notify%20%E2%80%98critical%20telecommunication%20infrastructure%E2%80%99%20and%20issue%20measures%20related%20to%20the%20protection%20of%20such%20telecommunication%20networks%20and%20services.%20Protection%20measures%20listed%20include%20collection%2C%20analysis%2C%20and%20dissemination%20of%20traffic%20data%2C%20wherein%20%E2%80%98traffic%20data%E2%80%99%20is%20defined%20as%20any%20data%20generated%2C%20transmitted%2C%20received%20or%20stored%20in%20telecommunication%20networks%20including%20data%20relating%20to%20the%20type%2C%20routing%2C%20duration%20or%20time%20of%20a%20telecommunication.%20This%20special%20categorisation%20and%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20notify%20them%2C%20provide%20rules%20for%20their%20standards%2C%20and%20give%20them%20directions%20did%20not%20exist%20in%20the%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%201885.%20Thus%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20retaining%20several%20provisions%20that%20centralised%20power%20and%20control%20with%20the%20Executive%2C%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20has%20created%20new%20ones%20that%20does%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClause%2043%20is%20reflective%20of%20this%20effort%20as%20it%20confers%20quasi-judicial%20powers%20to%20any%20officer%20authorised%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Esearch%20any%20building%2C%20vehicle%2C%20vessel%2C%20aircraft%20or%20place%20in%20which%20he%20has%20reason%20to%20believe%20that%20any%20unauthorised%20telecommunication%20network%E2%80%A6.%20in%20respect%20of%20which%20an%20offence%20punishable%20under%20section%2042%20has%20been%20committed%2C%20is%20kept%20or%20concealed%20and%20take%20possession%20thereof.%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20Such%20search%20and%20seizure%20powers%20are%20accompanied%20with%20the%20power%20to%20summon%20information%2C%20documents%2C%20or%20records%20in%20possession%20or%20control%20of%20any%20authorised%20entity%20if%20it%20is%20believed%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20be%20necessary%20for%20any%20pending%20or%20apprehended%20civil%20or%20criminal%20proceedings%20%5BClause%2044%5D.%20Such%20powers%2C%20non-existent%20in%20the%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%201885%2C%20may%20be%20open%20to%20misuse%20due%20to%20its%20ambiguous%20phrasing%2C%20absence%20of%20clear%20parameters%20of%20information%20that%20may%20be%20revealed%2C%20and%20overbroad%20grounds%20for%20revealing%20information%20due%20to%20the%20use%20of%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%9Capprehended%E2%80%9D.%20This%20vagueness%20may%20lead%20to%20overbroad%20requests%20for%20disclosure%20which%20could%20result%20in%20the%20violation%20of%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20of%20users%2C%20especially%20if%20it%20is%20applicable%20to%20internet%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMissed%20opportunity%20for%20surveillance%20and%20suspension%20reform%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20replication%20of%20language%20from%20the%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%201885%20%5BSection%205(2)%5D%20to%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20%5BClause%2020(2)(a)%5D%2C%20maintaining%20surveillance%20powers%20without%20any%20meaningful%20oversight%20or%20accountability%20processes.%20This%20centralises%20power%20in%20the%20Union%20and%20State%20Executive%20and%20is%20contrary%20to%20Supreme%20Court%20judgements%20and%20advances%20in%20surveillance%20regulations%20in%20comparative%2C%20common%20law%20jurisdictions%20(see%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2013%2F12%2F18%2Fsurveillance-and-privacy-in-india-iv-analysing-the-landmark-pucl-judgment%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprivacylibrary.ccgnlud.org%2Fcase%2Fjustice-ks-puttaswamy-ors-vs-union-of-india-ors%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fsurveillance-reform-pdpb%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Through%20Clause%2020(2)(b)%2C%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20cements%20the%20internet%20suspension%20power%20with%20the%20DoT%20without%20putting%20in%20place%20any%20of%20the%20procedural%20safeguards%20directed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20%3Cem%3EAnuradha%20Bhasin%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%20(2020)%20%5B3%20SCC%20637%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Information%20Technology%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fconcerned-with-frequent-internet-suspensions-parliamentary-committee-recommends-an-overhaul%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20also%20misses%20an%20opportunity%20to%20fix%20the%20shortcomings%20of%20the%20Temporary%20Suspension%20of%20Telecom%20Services%20(Public%20Emergency%20or%20Public%20Safety)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdot.gov.in%2Fcirculars%2Ftemporary-suspension-telecom-services-public-emergency-or-public-safety-rules-2017%5C%22%3ERules%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%202017.%20If%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20becomes%20applicable%20to%20online%20communication%20services%2C%20service%20providers%20such%20as%20Whatsapp%2C%20Signal%20etc.%2C%20which%20adopt%20the%20privacy%20protecting%20practice%20of%20End-to-End%20encryption%20(%E2%80%9CE2EE%E2%80%9D)%2C%20may%20also%20be%20required%20to%20intercept%2C%20detain%2C%20disclose%2C%20or%20suspend%20any%20message%2C%20wherein%20%E2%80%9Cmessage%E2%80%9D%20is%20defined%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eany%20sign%2C%20signal%2C%20writing%2C%20text%2C%20image%2C%20sound%2C%20video%2C%20data%20stream%2C%20intelligence%20or%20information%20sent%20through%20telecommunication%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20%5BClause%202(g)%5D.%20The%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20has%20failed%20to%20introduce%20improvements%20in%20the%20surveillance%20and%20internet%20shutdown%20architecture%20of%20the%20country%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20privacy%2C%20transparency%2C%20and%20accountability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUsers%20in%20the%20eye%20of%20the%20storm%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20penalty%20imposed%20on%20users%20for%20using%20unauthorised%20telecommunication%20services%2C%20either%20knowingly%20or%20having%20reason%20to%20believe%20it%20to%20be%20unauthorised%2C%20has%20been%20increased%20from%20Rs%2050%20in%20the%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%201885%20and%20Rs%201%20lakh%20in%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%20to%20a%20hefty%2010%20Lakh%20in%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20%5BThird%20Schedule%5D.%20The%20ground%20%E2%80%9Chaving%20reason%20to%20believe%20so%E2%80%9D%20may%20be%20misused%20and%20may%20put%20the%20user%20at%20a%20disadvantage%20as%20it%20appears%20to%20place%20the%20burden%20on%20them%20to%20prove%20lack%20of%20knowledge%20about%20the%20authorisation%20status%20of%20any%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETroubling%20patterns%20of%20delegated%20legislation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20like%20several%20of%20the%20legislations%20and%20draft%20bills%20released%20in%20the%20recent%20past%2C%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20suffers%20from%20excessive%20delegation%20by%20according%20the%20Union%20government%20overbroad%20rule-making%20powers%20without%20introducing%20adequate%20safeguards.%20While%20some%20instances%20of%20delegated%20legislation%20are%20justifiable%2C%20even%20necessary%2C%20at%20several%20instances%20out%20of%20the%20total%2046%20instances%2C%20specificity%20in%20the%20Bill%20is%20left%20to%20future%20rulemaking.%20Leaving%20relevant%20clarifications%20open%20to%20details%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20prescribed%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cnotified%E2%80%9D%20in%20certain%20instances%20such%20as%20providing%20exemption%20from%20and%20terms%20and%20conditions%20for%20authorisation%2C%20specifying%20duration%2C%20and%20manner%20of%20interception%2C%20disclosure%2C%20and%20suspension%20of%20telecommunication%20services%2C%20etc.%20contribute%20to%20increased%20uncertainty%2C%20vagueness%2C%20and%20raise%20concerns%20around%20arbitrary%20rule-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20improvements%20do%20exist%20in%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023.%20For%20instance%2C%20an%20attempt%20to%20dilute%20TRAI%E2%80%99s%20powers%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20governance%20of%20this%20sector%20introduced%20in%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%20has%20been%20reviewed%20and%20improved%20on%20in%20the%202023%20bill.%20The%20controversial%20provision%20in%20the%202022%20version%20allowing%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20sender%20of%20a%20message%20using%20telecommunication%20services%20to%20be%20made%20available%20to%20the%20user%20receiving%20such%20message%2C%20in%20such%20form%20as%20may%20be%20prescribed%2C%20has%20been%20removed%20in%C2%A0%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%23KillTheBill%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20like%20its%202022%20counterpart%2C%20has%20retained%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fthe-draft-indian-telecommunication-bill%2F%5C%22%3Ecolonial%20roots%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20missed%20an%20opportune%20moment%20for%20bringing%20about%20reform.%20The%20DoT%20must%20thus%20publicly%20release%20the%20comments%20received%20by%20it%20during%20the%20consultation%20on%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20transparency%20and%20accountability%2C%20so%20the%20stakeholders%20can%20gain%20insight%20into%20the%20DoT%E2%80%99s%20reasoning%20for%20holding%20on%20to%20provisions%20of%20an%20archaic%20law.%20Secondly%2C%20we%20urge%20the%20DoT%20to%20withdraw%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20and%20replace%20it%20with%20a%20right-centric%20version%20that%20protects%20and%20promotes%20individual%20rights.%20This%20version%20must%20be%20accompanied%20with%20a%20white%20paper%2F%20explanatory%20note%20with%20justifications%20and%20reasoning%20for%20introducing%20any%20changes%20introduced%20in%20comparison%20with%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%20of%202022%20as%20well%20as%202023.%20The%20DoT%20must%20also%20hold%20another%20consultation%2C%20that%20is%20broad%2C%20multi-city%2C%20in-person%20stakeholder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20is%20slated%20for%20passage%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20today%2C%20i.e.%20December%2020.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20crucial%20voice%20of%20the%20suspended%20140%2B%20opposition%20Members%20of%20Parliament%20and%20in%20light%20of%20the%20current%20state%20of%20chaos%2C%20disarray%2C%20protest%2C%20and%20walk%20outs%20in%20the%20Parliament%2C%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20must%20not%20be%20passed.%20We%20also%20recommend%20the%20Union%20Government%20to%20appoint%20a%20Law%20Commission%20and%2For%20an%20unbiased%2C%20independent%20Standing%20Committee%20or%20expert%20body%20to%20look%20into%20the%20kinds%20of%20reforms%20needed%20for%20the%20telecommunication%20sector.%20Finally%2C%20the%20clarification%20about%20online%20communication%20services%20being%20excluded%20from%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20bill%20must%20be%20explicitly%20and%20clearly%20added%20in%20the%20text%20of%20the%20bill%20itself%2C%20and%20not%20be%20inserted%20in%20subsequent%2C%20not%20enforceable%20FAQs%20(frequently%20asked%20questions)%20or%20clarified%20through%20verbal%20statements%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.exchange4media.com%2Famp%2Fdigital-news%2Fott-excluded-from-telecom-services-purview-in-new-draft-of-telecom-bill-2023-131514.html%5C%22%3EUnion%20Minister%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20unnamed%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftelecom.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolicy%2Fno-decision-yet-on-having-similar-rules-for-otts-and-telcos-official%2F106138191%5C%22%3Esenior%20officials%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETejasi%20Panjiar%20is%20Associate%20Policy%20Counsel%20and%20Prateek%20Waghre%20is%20Executive%20Director%20at%20the%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703068248000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20154844%2Fsunset-5423633_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftelecom-bill-2023-is-a-repackaged-version-of-the-archaic-colonial-law%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20like%20its%202022%20count